WEBVTT

00:06.200 --> 00:07.640
[crowd murmurs]

00:07.720 --> 00:09.000
[gavel bangs]

00:08.000 --> 00:18.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:09.080 --> 00:10.760
- [Pepsu] But, Your Honour.
- [Shubhkela] No, no.

00:10.840 --> 00:12.520
- [Pepsu] Your Honour.
- [Shubhkela] Honourably acquitted.

00:12.600 --> 00:15.760
State of Delhi versus Sajjan Patnaik.

00:15.840 --> 00:17.920
The accused is hereby
honourably acquitted.

00:18.000 --> 00:20.120
Your Honour? An acquittal for him?

00:20.200 --> 00:22.040
The accused is absconding on bail.

00:22.120 --> 00:24.160
Closing arguments have been made.

00:24.240 --> 00:26.840
The verdict has been pending
for three years.

00:26.920 --> 00:30.160
So until the police catch him,
should the court be left in limbo?

00:30.240 --> 00:31.280
Yes, Mr PP?

00:31.360 --> 00:35.440
Why are we wasting the court's time
chasing these petty scammers? Huh?

00:35.520 --> 00:37.840
Your Honour, the police have a request.

00:39.160 --> 00:42.440
Just… one last chance
to catch the culprit.

00:43.200 --> 00:45.600
Your Honour, it's fine
if you don't give me a chance.

00:46.400 --> 00:50.400
Just make a note in the order sheet
that officer Pepsu requested one.

00:50.480 --> 00:51.640
All right.

00:52.200 --> 00:54.600
The case will be disposed of after a week.

00:55.720 --> 00:58.360
It's not like you're going
to find Sajjan Patnaik.

01:00.400 --> 01:01.480
Adjourned.

01:03.000 --> 01:05.360
Noor Bano versus Sharafat Ali.

01:06.720 --> 01:09.720
The People's Court has only one purpose.

01:10.560 --> 01:13.040
Everyone wins. No one loses.

01:13.120 --> 01:14.600
- [grunting]
- [clamouring]

01:15.960 --> 01:17.600
Hey, hey! What are you doing?

01:17.680 --> 01:19.960
Hey, what are you--
Hey! What are you people doing?

01:20.040 --> 01:21.840
This is the People's Court.

01:21.920 --> 01:25.440
This isn't where cases are tried.
This is where negotiations are done.

01:26.040 --> 01:30.520
The two of you would have to work together
and find a solution. Okay?

01:30.600 --> 01:31.720
[howls]

01:31.800 --> 01:33.920
Look, we're here to help you
reach a settlement.

01:35.160 --> 01:37.840
- Next.
- [Topo] This is a national level event.

01:37.920 --> 01:40.680
Judges are coming from all over
to this place for judicial training.

01:41.160 --> 01:44.520
As per tradition, you should send
the senior-most judge in Patparganj.

01:45.040 --> 01:47.640
Mr Bainsla said I should send
a meritorious judge,

01:47.720 --> 01:49.040
not the senior-most one.

01:49.120 --> 01:52.640
Your Honour, in the workplace,
merit is based on seniority,

01:52.720 --> 01:54.000
not on actual merit.

01:54.080 --> 01:57.200
Yes, but only people with merit
are truly meritorious.

01:57.280 --> 01:59.720
I-It's very unfair, Your Honour.
It's very unfair.

01:59.800 --> 02:01.880
The system is full of people
who have no merit.

02:01.960 --> 02:04.040
In fact, they weren't even selected
based on merit.

02:04.120 --> 02:06.120
Don't they have the right
to be meritorious?

02:06.600 --> 02:07.840
On what grounds?

02:09.120 --> 02:10.280
S-Seniority.

02:10.360 --> 02:11.640
[sighs]

02:12.120 --> 02:15.960
Mr Kela was elevated to this court
from District Court.

02:16.040 --> 02:18.280
Imagine if he were a chief guest
at his own court,

02:18.360 --> 02:21.440
what an…
what an amazing surprise it would be.

02:21.520 --> 02:23.920
You just call them up
and recommend his name.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.120
[Pepsu] Your Honour, we have a problem.

02:26.200 --> 02:28.920
A few days ago, we nabbed
an associate of Sajjan Patnaik.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.640
- He gave us his new number. 6-3-2-1--
- Get to the point, Pepsu, please.

02:32.720 --> 02:34.880
That number was traced this morning, sir.

02:35.760 --> 02:37.000
The location is here.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.840
So are you trying to tell me

02:42.760 --> 02:47.560
that the absconding criminal is right here
in the court premises at this time?

02:51.200 --> 02:53.320
Pepsu, how will we find him? It's…

02:53.400 --> 02:55.040
It's the People's Court today.

02:55.840 --> 02:56.840
He must be…

03:03.960 --> 03:05.960
[opening theme music plays]

03:17.960 --> 03:19.080
[music ends]

03:19.160 --> 03:21.880
It's my fault, Sujata. It's my fault.

03:22.800 --> 03:25.200
I should never have made
Ani and Varsha sit together.

03:25.680 --> 03:26.680
Bring it here.

03:26.760 --> 03:28.120
I'm a fool.

03:28.200 --> 03:31.000
\[Sujata] You're not a fool.
It's Varsha who's the fool.

03:31.080 --> 03:32.760
Come on. Who breaks up over food, man?

03:32.840 --> 03:35.240
\Every Sunday,
the choreographer comes to teach me.

03:35.960 --> 03:39.160
\All my neighbours know I'm doing
a solo dance performance at my wedding.

03:41.080 --> 03:43.040
\Now no one's going to want
to see my moves.

03:44.040 --> 03:45.040
Aw.

03:45.120 --> 03:46.520
[phone rings]

03:47.760 --> 03:48.960
[Sujata] Is it Varsha?

03:49.040 --> 03:50.880
It's Mr Tyagi. I'll talk to him later.

03:51.440 --> 03:52.640
Vishwas!

03:53.400 --> 03:54.880
[stammers]

03:54.960 --> 03:56.600
It must be something important.

03:56.680 --> 03:59.120
Yes, Tyagi, sir. Yes. Y-Yes, I'm coming.

03:59.200 --> 04:01.000
[panting]

04:01.080 --> 04:03.640
I'm coming, sir. Yes. On the way. Yeah.

04:03.720 --> 04:06.360
Where's he off to? Didn't even say hi.

04:07.240 --> 04:09.200
Hmm. Stop acting all innocent.

04:09.280 --> 04:10.760
Who broke off the engagement?

04:11.400 --> 04:13.440
- [gasps]
- [scoffs]

04:13.520 --> 04:15.280
[stammers] But… listen…

04:15.360 --> 04:17.280
- [Tyagi] A con man in the court premises?
- Huh?

04:17.360 --> 04:19.760
This is scandalous.
We'll be ripped apart by the media.

04:19.840 --> 04:21.080
[PP] Yes, Your Honour.

04:21.160 --> 04:22.360
[Tyagi] This is very serious.

04:22.440 --> 04:23.440
Hello, sir.

04:23.520 --> 04:25.320
Yes, Vishwas. We were waiting for you.

04:25.800 --> 04:30.280
Look, you will delegate all the work for
the People's Court to someone else today,

04:30.360 --> 04:33.720
and spend the whole day accompanying
Officer Pepsu and his team.

04:33.800 --> 04:35.560
Con man Sajjan Patnaik is here in court.

04:36.160 --> 04:38.000
What? Con… Con man?

04:40.280 --> 04:42.880
No problem, sir.
Uh, I just need a picture of him.

04:42.960 --> 04:45.360
I'll have it posted all over the place.
We'll get him in a jiffy.

04:45.440 --> 04:48.160
Pictures? There are none.

04:49.720 --> 04:51.080
[stammers] No pictures?

04:51.160 --> 04:54.200
The thing is, a few months ago,
I got digitally arrested.

04:55.680 --> 04:59.400
The scammer said, "I am from the CBI
so you're being investigated."

05:00.400 --> 05:04.440
Even though my record is absolutely clean,
I gave him 200 grand.

05:05.080 --> 05:06.520
And access to the whole system.

05:07.120 --> 05:08.160
All the data was erased.

05:08.240 --> 05:09.760
Data erased? Government data?

05:09.840 --> 05:12.400
- We've ordered a sketch.
- No, no. Sketches are no good, sir.

05:12.480 --> 05:14.880
- Come on.
- I mean, it causes confusion, sir.

05:16.760 --> 05:20.120
Thousands of people come to court.
Lawyers, the police, staff.

05:20.200 --> 05:23.040
And there'll be even more people today.
The People's Court is in session.

05:23.120 --> 05:25.240
How will we find him?
Do you have a strategy?

05:25.320 --> 05:26.960
[sips]

05:30.520 --> 05:31.680
Hope.

05:32.160 --> 05:33.160
[sighs]

05:33.240 --> 05:36.600
Vishwas, this matter should stay
within these four walls.

05:36.680 --> 05:37.680
Yes, sir.

05:38.160 --> 05:40.160
The purpose of having a People's Court is

05:40.240 --> 05:42.480
to make the court accessible
to the people.

05:42.960 --> 05:46.080
At no time should they ever feel
that they are unsafe.

05:46.160 --> 05:47.600
You're right.

05:47.680 --> 05:50.000
So make sure you update me
every half an hour.

05:50.080 --> 05:52.360
And me every 28 minutes.

05:54.840 --> 05:55.840
Sure.

05:57.920 --> 05:59.920
[Sujata]
So the matter is property related.

06:00.000 --> 06:04.640
Yes. Now that Kulwant is gone,
that bitch wants our home.

06:04.720 --> 06:08.840
And home would be
P-521 Greater Kailash, correct?

06:09.480 --> 06:10.800
Top floor with terrace.

06:12.480 --> 06:14.720
- Mr Danish, I have another question.
- Come on!

06:15.200 --> 06:17.000
Have you ever been in a marriage before?

06:17.080 --> 06:20.160
- No.
- So by bitch, you mean Kulwant's wife?

06:20.240 --> 06:21.240
Yes.

06:21.320 --> 06:23.880
But, sir, women can't get married
to each other.

06:24.800 --> 06:27.040
- Uh, act--
- Kulwant was a man.

06:28.120 --> 06:29.120
My partner.

06:29.800 --> 06:31.800
His wife. The bitch.

06:32.680 --> 06:33.680
Huh?

06:34.680 --> 06:36.400
Sujata, Kulwant was gay.

06:36.480 --> 06:39.120
Shut up! Don't talk like that
about a dead man.

06:39.200 --> 06:41.400
And why not? That's our identity.

06:41.480 --> 06:42.760
You're gay?

06:43.880 --> 06:45.560
But you seem pretty normal.

06:45.640 --> 06:48.200
You aren't dressed in bright colours,
your right ear isn't pierced,

06:48.280 --> 06:50.640
your arms are quite hairy.
You look pretty manly to me.

06:51.240 --> 06:52.880
Your arms are quite hairy too.

06:52.960 --> 06:55.200
- [Law laughs]
- What does that make you?

06:55.280 --> 06:57.680
I'm sorry, sir. She didn't mean
to offend you like that.

06:58.160 --> 07:00.160
Not at all, sir. I never discriminate.

07:00.640 --> 07:02.520
No matter who they are,
they're my clients.

07:02.600 --> 07:04.760
- Be they straight or gay--
- [scoffs] Sujata!

07:05.600 --> 07:07.080
That's offensive.

07:07.160 --> 07:08.880
Sir, look, I'm very sorry.

07:08.960 --> 07:10.680
She really didn't mean to say that.

07:10.760 --> 07:12.320
Pramila is contesting this will.

07:13.440 --> 07:17.000
And according to this will,
Kulwant left the house to me.

07:17.080 --> 07:19.720
I know the court has
a strong prejudice against us.

07:21.040 --> 07:22.840
That's why I'm willing to compromise.

07:23.440 --> 07:26.520
Twenty percent of the property value,
I will pay to her.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.040
But I want to keep my home.

07:29.120 --> 07:30.880
But how is it his home, sir?

07:30.960 --> 07:33.840
For the last 30 years,
I am the one who's been Mrs Kulwant.

07:34.440 --> 07:35.480
Miss Pramila,

07:35.560 --> 07:40.240
when you found out that
your husband Kulwant bats for both teams,

07:40.320 --> 07:41.680
why didn't you divorce him?

07:43.800 --> 07:46.280
[clears throat] My father was a plumber.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.240
But thanks to my own efforts,

07:48.320 --> 07:50.400
I managed to marry into
an upper-class family.

07:50.880 --> 07:51.920
And for what?

07:52.000 --> 07:54.560
Just so I could give up everything
and become independent? Huh?

07:55.880 --> 07:58.720
Kulwant paid me a cheque
of 200 grand every month.

07:58.800 --> 08:00.080
I'd have settled for 70 grand.

08:00.160 --> 08:01.680
And I for seven grand.

08:03.000 --> 08:05.080
Look, he told me
the cheques wouldn't stop coming.

08:05.160 --> 08:07.800
And now he's gone,
leaving the top floor to Danish. Huh?

08:07.880 --> 08:11.200
I mean, for so many years women have been
fighting hard to get property rights!

08:11.280 --> 08:13.880
For what? So that it can just be
given away to gay men?

08:13.960 --> 08:14.960
Look, ma'am,

08:15.040 --> 08:17.360
- on paper, you are Mr Kulwant's wife.
- That's right!

08:17.440 --> 08:19.760
And according to personal law,
the property of the deceased

08:19.840 --> 08:21.160
- goes to the spouse.
- Of course.

08:21.240 --> 08:23.480
And this Danish is just a… you know… a…

08:23.560 --> 08:24.760
What do you call a male mistress?

08:24.840 --> 08:26.480
- A "manstress".
- Yes, "manstress".

08:26.560 --> 08:28.360
- Danish is just a--
- But, sir, why did you ask me?

08:28.440 --> 08:29.680
[Mintu, Shambhu laugh]

08:29.760 --> 08:31.600
- [Mintu] I thought maybe you--
- Look here, sir!

08:31.680 --> 08:33.720
I want my share of the property.

08:34.240 --> 08:35.240
Fine.

08:35.720 --> 08:39.720
I am willing to part with 20%
for that "manstress".

08:39.800 --> 08:41.640
You just get him to compromise.

08:41.720 --> 08:43.240
Why should we always compromise?

08:44.360 --> 08:46.680
First, you force us into
heterosexual marriages.

08:47.800 --> 08:51.360
And then when we come out,
you refuse to recognise gay marriages.

08:51.440 --> 08:53.960
And then you say
the spouse has all the rights.

08:54.040 --> 08:55.680
Now you tell me, is that fair?

08:55.760 --> 08:58.800
- Sir, that's unfair, but legal.
- Yeah.

08:58.880 --> 09:01.880
Sir, where's it written in the will
that the two of you were gay?

09:03.360 --> 09:06.200
And, uh, what we also realised today is,

09:06.280 --> 09:09.680
uh, just by appearance,
you can't tell who is gay and who isn't.

09:09.760 --> 09:11.200
[whispers] Sujata.

09:11.280 --> 09:12.760
Sir, I've got a great idea.

09:13.280 --> 09:16.280
But for that, I'm afraid
you'll have to go back into the drawer.

09:17.120 --> 09:18.760
You mean closet.

09:19.360 --> 09:21.760
You can't ask him
to hide his identity like that.

09:22.600 --> 09:24.360
It must have been really hard
for him to come--

09:24.440 --> 09:25.760
Actually, it's okay.

09:26.280 --> 09:28.680
I spent my whole life
acting straight for nothing.

09:29.880 --> 09:33.600
At least this time, I'll get my home back.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.360
[officer 1] Show me camera number four.

09:37.440 --> 09:39.560
[officer 2, through radio]
Yes, number seven is clear.

09:39.640 --> 09:41.160
Camera number five.

09:41.240 --> 09:42.640
[officer 2 speaks indistinctly]

09:43.560 --> 09:44.560
What is this?

09:44.640 --> 09:46.600
[through radio] Now, who put this
in front of the camera?

09:46.680 --> 09:47.680
[bangs]

09:48.840 --> 09:50.280
Idiot.

09:50.360 --> 09:52.440
[Rajesh] So what if
there's a mole on her face?

09:54.000 --> 09:56.640
The card is in her bag,
and you have seized it.

09:56.720 --> 09:58.160
Why are you holding her here?

09:58.680 --> 10:00.120
Her face is a good match.

10:00.640 --> 10:02.440
She even has a mole on her right cheek.

10:09.640 --> 10:12.720
Sajjan Patnaik is a man.

10:12.800 --> 10:16.120
But he could've entered the court
disguised as a woman. What then?

10:17.000 --> 10:18.160
Ah.

10:18.240 --> 10:19.560
Bloody fool.

10:21.200 --> 10:23.280
You can leave. Carry on.

10:24.080 --> 10:25.240
[Pepsu] Mr Topo.

10:26.320 --> 10:29.520
I have figured out the correct way
to find Sajjan Patnaik.

10:30.040 --> 10:31.520
- Which is?
- Wanna see?

10:33.000 --> 10:34.320
Sajjan Patnaik!

10:37.920 --> 10:40.080
All those who've turned, pull them aside.

10:40.160 --> 10:41.800
- Yes, sir.
- Hey, hang on. Hang on.

10:43.600 --> 10:44.600
Pepsu!

10:48.160 --> 10:50.320
Where do they find idiots like this?

10:50.400 --> 10:52.400
- [Pepsu, through radio] Vishwas.
- Everyone needs to form a queue.

10:52.480 --> 10:56.320
- Entry will be only from the main gate.
- Walk in one-by-one. This way, please.

10:56.400 --> 10:59.120
Look, Pepsu, you can't make them enter
and exit from the same gate.

10:59.200 --> 11:00.560
There'll be a stampede!

11:00.640 --> 11:04.280
Stampedes only happen when people
are served free food, not free justice.

11:04.360 --> 11:06.840
- Vishwas, listen, I'm so sorry.
- Hello. Yeah.

11:06.920 --> 11:08.640
I-I didn't realise that Varsha would--

11:08.720 --> 11:11.600
Uh, I've got tons of stuff to do.
I'll talk-- I'll see you later. Yeah.

11:11.680 --> 11:13.000
- Vishwas?
- Uh, Pepsu, I'm telling you,

11:13.080 --> 11:14.720
we are going to have
a stampede here. You--

11:14.800 --> 11:17.800
Sujata, he is not even talking to me.
What have I done wrong?

11:17.880 --> 11:21.040
Ani, please just help me with this case
and I'll make sure he talks to you.

11:21.120 --> 11:22.280
Who's the wife's lawyer?

11:22.360 --> 11:23.960
How will I know who the lawyer is?

11:24.040 --> 11:26.040
The People's Court doesn't
put up a cause list.

11:26.120 --> 11:28.600
And there's such a huge crowd
I can't even see the other party.

11:28.680 --> 11:32.320
[laughs] Let them come, whoever they are.
The case is already ours! Come on.

11:32.400 --> 11:34.280
Hey, step aside. Let the lawyers through.
Move! Move!

11:34.360 --> 11:38.160
All right, next case.
Pramila Kapoor versus…

11:38.240 --> 11:40.520
- Present, Your Honour.
- …Danish Chandani.

11:40.600 --> 11:41.680
Yes, Your Honour.

11:43.880 --> 11:46.760
You're both from the same chamber, right?

11:46.840 --> 11:48.400
Are you representing Pramila as well?

11:48.480 --> 11:50.960
Are you guys getting money
from both parties? Huh?

11:51.040 --> 11:53.120
Ma'am, the score is 14 all right now.

11:53.200 --> 11:56.200
Sir, whoever resolves the most cases
gets to name the chamber.

11:57.040 --> 12:00.360
[clears throat] Your Honour,
our chamber is representing Miss Pramila.

12:00.440 --> 12:03.840
[scoffs] No, Your Honour,
our chamber is representing Mr. Danish.

12:03.920 --> 12:07.760
Look, look. If this was court,
I would not have allowed this at all.

12:07.840 --> 12:09.040
Conflict of interest.

12:09.120 --> 12:12.080
But today, we all have
the same interest here, right?

12:12.160 --> 12:13.320
Compromise.

12:13.840 --> 12:15.840
So tell me. Should we do it?

12:16.440 --> 12:18.360
- Your Honour, uh--
- Of course, Your Honour.

12:18.440 --> 12:20.120
They should definitely do it, sir.

12:20.200 --> 12:21.680
There are many precedents, Your Honour,

12:21.760 --> 12:23.560
where the property has gone
not to the mistress.

12:23.640 --> 12:24.840
It has gone to the wife.

12:25.360 --> 12:27.760
And anyway, Mr Danish is
just his "manstress".

12:28.800 --> 12:30.000
"Manstress" meaning?

12:30.080 --> 12:31.400
[stammers]

12:31.480 --> 12:34.200
A mistress who's a man, Your Honour.

12:34.800 --> 12:35.880
Who's a man?

12:35.960 --> 12:38.440
Well, uh, someone on the side?

12:39.240 --> 12:41.960
- A man on the side?
- [Order] A male mistress!

12:43.800 --> 12:46.960
Your Honour, we were best friends.

12:47.040 --> 12:49.560
- Best friends? Your Honour, he's my rival.
- [Mintu] Best friends.

12:49.640 --> 12:52.120
And they were having
a homosexual relationship.

12:52.200 --> 12:53.480
[Sujata] No, Your Honour!

12:53.560 --> 12:56.680
It wasn't homosexual,
it was "bromosexual".

12:57.320 --> 13:00.240
Your Honour, you tell me.
Do I appear gay to you?

13:00.320 --> 13:02.160
Uh, well, maybe a little--

13:02.240 --> 13:04.120
Your Honour,
for the sake of a few square feet,

13:04.200 --> 13:05.960
he's willing to betray
his whole community.

13:06.040 --> 13:07.280
Mr. Danish is gay.

13:07.800 --> 13:09.600
Your Honour, my client is being defamed.

13:09.680 --> 13:12.400
That's a very primitive
way of thinking, Ms Sujata.

13:12.480 --> 13:16.440
In today's day and age,
calling someone gay is hardly defamation.

13:16.520 --> 13:17.720
[Sujata] Sorry, uh…

13:18.640 --> 13:21.800
Your Honour, I hope you don't mind…
but you seem a little gay today.

13:21.880 --> 13:24.080
- What kind of nonsense is that!
- [giggles]

13:24.160 --> 13:26.200
Can't you see all this hair on my arms?

13:26.280 --> 13:28.600
Your Honour, the fact of the matter is,

13:28.680 --> 13:30.280
that even after he got married,

13:30.360 --> 13:32.360
Kulwant preferred to spend time
with his friends

13:32.440 --> 13:34.240
because his wife only married him
for his money.

13:34.320 --> 13:37.840
So it's only natural that after his death,
he left his property

13:37.920 --> 13:40.480
to Danish Chandani,
who was his best friend.

13:40.560 --> 13:42.600
- And despite all of this…
- She's lying through her teeth.

13:42.680 --> 13:45.280
…Mr Danish is more than willing

13:45.800 --> 13:47.880
- to pay her 20 percent of his share.
- Yes, sir.

13:47.960 --> 13:49.080
Justified.

13:49.160 --> 13:51.320
Your Honour, now we're going to take 100%.

13:51.400 --> 13:53.360
You've insulted my client
in front of everyone!

13:53.440 --> 13:55.040
- Are you're not insulting him?
- What did I do?

13:55.120 --> 13:56.880
- What was that crack about being gay?
- But he is gay.

13:56.960 --> 14:00.120
- You don't have any manners at all.
- You're the one who has no manners.

14:00.200 --> 14:04.160
"The people's court has one sole purpose.
Everyone wins, no one loses."

14:04.240 --> 14:06.840
Look, if you people had
no intention of compromising,

14:06.920 --> 14:08.560
why did you come here at all?

14:08.640 --> 14:11.520
I think it's high time
all these pre-litigation matters

14:11.600 --> 14:13.480
are totally banned
from the people's court.

14:13.560 --> 14:15.600
You both are from the same chamber,

14:15.680 --> 14:17.440
and don't know the basics
of the People's Court?

14:17.520 --> 14:18.800
- Your Honour--
- Ms Sujata,

14:18.880 --> 14:20.840
if you two want to make a scene,
please do it inside!

14:20.920 --> 14:22.800
That's it. I'm done. Next.

14:22.880 --> 14:25.560
Vivek Tiwari versus Babita Lachda.

14:27.520 --> 14:30.360
[Munshi] I thought that
by competing with each other,

14:30.440 --> 14:32.200
you would learn from each other.

14:32.280 --> 14:35.000
You'd find each other's
strengths and weaknesses.

14:35.560 --> 14:38.240
And the partnership would grow stronger.

14:38.840 --> 14:40.320
Which would benefit the chamber.

14:44.640 --> 14:47.320
But I made one mistake.

14:48.960 --> 14:53.920
I never imagined you two would have
so little consideration for the chamber.

14:55.400 --> 14:58.280
By taking both clients, from the same case

14:58.360 --> 15:01.000
you have proofed to everyone
that what was just a doubt

15:01.080 --> 15:02.920
is now undoubtedly confirmed.

15:04.280 --> 15:07.720
That after Visheshwar,
this chamber has no future whatsoever.

15:07.800 --> 15:08.880
[sighs]

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:09.400 --> 15:12.360
By obsessing over
who will name this chamber,

15:12.440 --> 15:15.160
you have dragged its name
right into the dust!

15:15.240 --> 15:18.040
[melancholy music playing]

15:20.760 --> 15:23.280
I thought I would continue
for another five more years.

15:24.440 --> 15:25.480
And then retire.

15:28.080 --> 15:29.400
But now…

15:42.240 --> 15:43.680
[stammers] Sujata…

15:44.720 --> 15:46.480
I started this whole argument.

15:47.320 --> 15:48.440
This is all my fault.

15:48.520 --> 15:51.480
Let's decide whose fault it was
after we set it right.

15:53.880 --> 15:55.520
We tarnished the name, right?

15:56.040 --> 15:57.560
Then we're going to restore it.

15:59.200 --> 16:00.800
[Order] But, ma'am, how will we do it?

16:01.600 --> 16:05.160
Even if we give up one client,
our reputation will still be ruined.

16:06.360 --> 16:08.400
If the chamber's taken on both clients,

16:09.560 --> 16:10.680
then both have to win.

16:12.760 --> 16:14.200
What do you mean?

16:14.880 --> 16:15.880
The People's court.

16:15.960 --> 16:17.320
[intriguing music playing]

16:17.920 --> 16:19.560
Sir, didn't I tell you you can't meet him?

16:19.640 --> 16:20.960
You keep coming back!

16:21.040 --> 16:23.760
I told you I have to meet the PDJ!

16:23.840 --> 16:25.280
[Rajesh] Mr Topo.

16:25.360 --> 16:27.720
Uh, he says he wants to meet the PDJ.

16:27.800 --> 16:29.560
He keeps saying
he has some urgent work with him.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.120
Come in. Show me your ID.

16:37.520 --> 16:39.840
[intriguing music playing]

16:40.440 --> 16:41.800
Kailash Shubhkela.

16:41.880 --> 16:45.080
Uh… This is your name?

16:45.160 --> 16:48.280
Yes. I've only recently been elevated
from the District Court.

16:48.360 --> 16:49.920
Now step aside and let me in!

16:51.120 --> 16:54.120
Sir, one minute, I'll just confirm this
with the PDJ. One minute.

16:55.880 --> 16:59.280
Listen, Pepsu, this Sajjan Patnaik?
How old is he?

17:00.760 --> 17:01.880
Forty-four.

17:02.680 --> 17:04.280
So he was born in '81.

17:05.120 --> 17:06.400
And what's his height?

17:08.000 --> 17:09.160
5'9.

17:09.720 --> 17:11.000
I found the bastard.

17:11.520 --> 17:12.640
Bloody con man.

17:13.160 --> 17:15.320
[sucks teeth] Pepsu, we got him.

17:15.400 --> 17:17.120
[detector beeping]

17:17.200 --> 17:18.480
Hey, listen.

17:18.560 --> 17:20.240
From now on, don't trouble the judge.

17:22.080 --> 17:24.480
Come with me, sir.
The PDJ is waiting for you.

17:24.560 --> 17:25.720
- Come. Come on.
- Let us go.

17:28.520 --> 17:30.520
[music continues]

17:44.680 --> 17:45.800
What is your name?

17:47.720 --> 17:49.000
Kailash Shubhkela.

17:49.840 --> 17:51.160
[scoffs, chuckles]

17:51.240 --> 17:52.240
He's lying.

17:53.520 --> 17:55.200
His heartbeat has increased.

17:55.920 --> 17:58.160
Look, you people have
got me tied to a chair.

17:58.240 --> 17:59.680
Wouldn't your heartbeat increase?

17:59.760 --> 18:01.600
I'm telling the truth.

18:01.680 --> 18:04.600
You know what? You're more than
welcome to check my bag. You'll find my--

18:04.680 --> 18:06.480
- [Pepsu] Sure I'll check the bag.
- [PP] Hang on!

18:06.560 --> 18:09.160
Once the bag is opened
a snake will pop out

18:09.240 --> 18:10.720
and then you'll give us the slip, huh?

18:10.800 --> 18:11.800
Hmm?

18:11.880 --> 18:14.800
Yes. This bastard
did the same thing else were to.

18:14.880 --> 18:15.880
[Tyagi] Pepsu.

18:17.320 --> 18:18.600
S-Sorry, your Honour.

18:19.200 --> 18:20.280
No abusing.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.040
Why did you want to meet me?

18:22.120 --> 18:23.840
Remember you'd called the District Court

18:23.920 --> 18:25.920
regarding the judicial training event?

18:26.000 --> 18:28.040
- [Pepsu] The bastard knows everything.
- Uh-uh.

18:29.080 --> 18:31.880
He is very cunning, sir. Very cunning.

18:32.720 --> 18:34.880
But in my experience, people like him

18:34.960 --> 18:37.400
always wear a fake beard,
moustache and wig.

18:37.480 --> 18:39.200
I think we should do a thorough check.

18:39.280 --> 18:40.440
- [PP] Check him.
- [Pepsu] Yes, sir.

18:41.040 --> 18:42.760
[Shubhkela yelps] Hey! It's my own hair!

18:42.840 --> 18:45.760
[shouting]

18:46.440 --> 18:47.480
[stammers] He's…

18:47.560 --> 18:49.480
[grunting, screams]

18:49.560 --> 18:51.760
- Hey…
- [shouting continues]

18:51.840 --> 18:53.360
Uh… Okay, Pepsu, please stop.

18:53.440 --> 18:54.440
[shouts]

18:54.520 --> 18:57.160
- [panting]
- [Tyagi] Just stop. Uh… It's real hair.

18:57.240 --> 18:58.800
Yes, it is real. [chuckles]

18:58.880 --> 19:01.080
- What makes you think it's not real?
- Yeah, yeah.

19:01.160 --> 19:03.920
[inhales deeply]
I am Kailash Shubhkela, okay?

19:04.000 --> 19:06.720
I've been practising lawyer for 20 years.

19:06.800 --> 19:08.080
Don't any of you believe me?

19:08.160 --> 19:09.160
No.

19:09.240 --> 19:13.000
Then please go ahead
and check my bag. My ID is inside.

19:13.080 --> 19:15.240
- [PP] Go check.
- [Tyagi] Topo.

19:16.280 --> 19:18.600
- There could be a snake.
- Really?

19:18.680 --> 19:20.280
Yes.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.640
- [PP] That's what I said.
- [Tyagi] District Court…

19:22.720 --> 19:25.920
The president of the Bar Association there
is an old friend of mine.

19:26.440 --> 19:28.240
We can verify this right away.

19:28.320 --> 19:30.240
[line ringing]

19:31.600 --> 19:34.360
[chuckles] Mr Zaidi, hello.
How are you, sir?

19:34.440 --> 19:36.040
I'm fine, I'm fine.

19:36.120 --> 19:39.600
Well, actually, Mr Zaidi,
we have a gentleman here with us.

19:39.680 --> 19:43.520
He claims that he's a very well-known
lawyer at the District Court.

19:43.600 --> 19:45.400
Do you happen to know him?

19:49.880 --> 19:52.160
- Zaidi, sir!
- [PP chuckles]

19:52.240 --> 19:55.080
Zaidi, sir. It's me, Kailash.

19:55.160 --> 19:56.400
I'm Kailash!

19:57.840 --> 20:00.200
Hey! That's Mr Shubhkela!

20:00.280 --> 20:02.160
- But why have you tied him up, Tyagi?
- [stammering]

20:02.240 --> 20:04.680
Um, I'll talk to you a little later,
Mr Zaidi.

20:05.320 --> 20:07.360
- [Vishwas] Oh, my God.
- [Topo] Untie the judge.

20:07.440 --> 20:09.480
- Oh, my God. I'm sorry, sir.
- Sorry, sir.

20:10.760 --> 20:14.040
[Vishwas] Just settle Sir's hair, please.
No wonder his hair was not coming off.

20:14.120 --> 20:16.640
Uh… That's how they do it
in true crime shows. [chuckles]

20:17.600 --> 20:18.640
Piss off!

20:21.520 --> 20:22.520
Tyagi, sir.

20:23.480 --> 20:27.680
If he is the real Shubhkela,
then who… who's that judge?

20:32.840 --> 20:34.160
Sajjan Patnaik.

20:43.120 --> 20:45.600
Danish is still stuck
on my earlier strategy.

20:45.680 --> 20:48.160
He insists he'll walk into court
as a straight man.

20:48.240 --> 20:49.840
- He won't compro… Namaste.
- Namaste.

20:49.920 --> 20:52.080
He won't compromise on a single rupee.

20:52.160 --> 20:53.160
He just won't listen.

20:53.240 --> 20:55.160
And Pramila's just as adamant.

20:55.240 --> 20:58.720
She says, "First he took my husband,
and now he's defaming me in public."

20:58.800 --> 21:02.240
She wants to see Danish humiliated
in front of the entire court.

21:02.320 --> 21:05.760
You have to convince them somehow.
The People's Court ends in two hours.

21:05.840 --> 21:07.960
First of all,
the People's Court is voluntary.

21:08.040 --> 21:09.960
How will we get them to compromise?

21:10.600 --> 21:13.520
Voluntary can be made compulsory.

21:16.240 --> 21:17.800
It's a civil case.

21:17.880 --> 21:20.360
There's bound to be
a few irregularities somewhere.

21:20.440 --> 21:22.560
Tyagi used to say the same thing.

21:23.560 --> 21:26.120
Instill confidence
in a client who's scared,

21:26.720 --> 21:29.680
and strike fear in a client
who's confident.

21:30.280 --> 21:31.400
Exactly.

21:32.320 --> 21:33.640
Fear of punishment.

21:35.480 --> 21:37.000
Done strategy.

21:37.800 --> 21:39.840
Forget the lift,
there is fire compliance too.

21:39.920 --> 21:41.040
Who does all this crap?

21:41.120 --> 21:43.520
Sale deed, mutation certificate,
it's all there!

21:44.760 --> 21:47.240
[Mintu] We were trying to scare them
and we're getting screwed.

21:47.320 --> 21:48.920
How are we going to face Mr Munshi?

21:49.440 --> 21:51.320
Hold on. Wait a second.

21:53.960 --> 21:58.720
Why is Danish's bungalow so much higher
than the neighboring bungalow?

21:58.800 --> 22:00.480
- [Order] Meaning?
- [Mintu] Let's see.

22:01.080 --> 22:02.080
Look.

22:09.920 --> 22:11.880
- [Sujata] Well done, Ani.
- [chuckles]

22:11.960 --> 22:13.200
- Mintu?
- [Mintu] Yes.

22:13.280 --> 22:16.680
Confirm this with the registrar's office.
I'll go and get Mr Munshi.

22:16.760 --> 22:17.760
Okay. Great.

22:19.360 --> 22:21.880
Okay, Pepsu. I'm here. Pepsu, here.

22:21.960 --> 22:23.200
- But where is the judge?
- What's up?

22:23.280 --> 22:25.880
He went to the washroom half an hour ago.
He's not back yet.

22:25.960 --> 22:27.280
Has he given us the slip?

22:33.680 --> 22:34.680
\He's run away.

22:37.200 --> 22:38.840
\- He's gone.
- But where?

22:38.920 --> 22:39.920
\Motherfucker scooted!

22:40.000 --> 22:42.560
\In 2008 he committed fraud
as a tax officer.

22:43.600 --> 22:46.240
The lack of evidence
allowed him to get away.

22:46.320 --> 22:49.880
And in 2017,
he was running a fake bank branch.

22:49.960 --> 22:51.320
The man got's guts.

22:51.400 --> 22:53.960
This time he was handling
his own case as a judge.

22:54.040 --> 22:56.680
- So he could acquit himself and get away.
- Yeah.

22:56.760 --> 22:59.000
- His passport must've been seized by now.
- [PP] Of course.

22:59.080 --> 23:00.640
- [Vishwas] Tyagi, sir.
- Sir.

23:00.720 --> 23:02.200
- [Tyagi] Yes what, what?
- Tyagi, sir.

23:02.280 --> 23:03.480
- Tell him.
- What happened?

23:03.560 --> 23:05.200
- What, what? He…
- He's run off, sir.

23:05.280 --> 23:07.200
- He's run off?
- It's all his fault, sir.

23:07.280 --> 23:08.640
- My fault?
- What?

23:08.720 --> 23:11.280
I mean, he made it so obvious
with the whole army standing there.

23:11.360 --> 23:13.040
And the judge figured out his time was up.

23:13.120 --> 23:15.480
Damn it! You really are the limit!

23:16.280 --> 23:17.760
The pits.

23:17.840 --> 23:18.960
[Pepsu] With your permission, sir…

23:19.040 --> 23:20.560
We'll have to shut down
the People's Court.

23:20.640 --> 23:22.520
You see? He won't get away this time.

23:22.600 --> 23:24.080
Wait a minute. I'll call him.

23:24.160 --> 23:25.440
Huh?

23:25.520 --> 23:26.840
He won't answer, Your Honor.

23:29.120 --> 23:30.680
Be positive, Topo.

23:30.760 --> 23:31.960
[sighs]

23:34.400 --> 23:35.520
[line ringing]

23:38.520 --> 23:42.000
[automated voice] The person you are
trying to reach is not answering…

23:44.400 --> 23:45.800
[exhales deeply]

23:45.880 --> 23:47.960
[phone chimes]

23:48.040 --> 23:49.520
Hey! Huh…

23:51.920 --> 23:54.120
- Mr Kela?
- [Patnaik] Yes, Tyagi.

23:54.200 --> 23:55.920
I was in the bathroom. Tell me.

23:56.800 --> 24:00.800
I was wondering if you and I
could meet right now,

24:01.760 --> 24:03.360
- on the terrace.
- [inhales sharply]

24:06.040 --> 24:08.040
You carry on. [chuckles]

24:08.120 --> 24:10.400
I'll see you there.
I'll bring my special tea.

24:10.480 --> 24:12.000
Great. I'll be right there.

24:12.080 --> 24:13.320
Let's go, sir.

24:14.440 --> 24:15.960
No. I'd rather go alone.

24:16.040 --> 24:18.360
[inhales sharply] I'll be back soon.
You guys wait here.

24:18.440 --> 24:19.440
I can't believe this.

24:20.400 --> 24:22.160
Are the two of you really sure

24:22.240 --> 24:24.400
that you want to go court
over this property?

24:24.480 --> 24:25.520
- Yes.
- Yes.

24:25.600 --> 24:29.720
That's P-521 GK 2, top floor.

24:29.800 --> 24:31.040
And top floor would be?

24:31.120 --> 24:32.600
Third floor.

24:35.240 --> 24:37.840
So, according to the government records,

24:37.920 --> 24:40.440
the top floor is the second floor.

24:41.600 --> 24:44.640
And Zoning laws do not allow
any construction above that.

24:44.720 --> 24:46.080
How's that possible?

24:46.160 --> 24:48.400
We bought the third floor
directly from the builder.

24:48.480 --> 24:51.080
- I have all the documents.
- Someone sold the Taj Mahal

24:51.160 --> 24:52.400
by showing the right documents.

24:52.480 --> 24:54.600
Your construction is illegal, sir.

24:54.680 --> 24:56.720
And if this matter goes to court,

24:56.800 --> 24:59.760
the issue won't be property dispute,
but property demolition.

24:59.840 --> 25:02.360
- [Sujata] Hmm.
- And both of you will end up with nothing.

25:02.440 --> 25:05.920
So… Court or out of court?

25:11.400 --> 25:15.840
What you call a plan,
a paper or a property…

25:17.480 --> 25:18.960
was home to us.

25:19.040 --> 25:20.600
[soft music plays]

25:20.680 --> 25:23.400
With great difficulty,
we created a safe space,

25:23.480 --> 25:24.880
where we could be ourselves.

25:28.520 --> 25:30.920
I didn't expect any support
from anyone then,

25:32.160 --> 25:33.920
nor do I expect it now. [sighs]

25:35.840 --> 25:39.120
But all I expect from all of you
is to understand.

25:41.880 --> 25:43.280
I loved Kulwant.

25:46.320 --> 25:48.040
And this is all I have left of him.

25:51.000 --> 25:52.000
You take the house.

25:53.520 --> 25:54.920
I just want my share.

25:55.440 --> 25:57.000
Because I have a right to it.

25:57.520 --> 26:00.400
How will I pay the money?
I don't have that much.

26:00.480 --> 26:02.600
But Ms Pramila doesn't want that much.

26:02.680 --> 26:06.080
Just pay her 200,000 a month
as long as she's alive.

26:09.440 --> 26:11.280
I… I can do that.

26:11.360 --> 26:12.560
Matter settled.

26:12.640 --> 26:14.320
You get to keep your house,

26:14.400 --> 26:16.520
and you get 200,000 rupees a month.

26:16.600 --> 26:18.880
Just as Mr Kulwant
had promised both of you.

26:18.960 --> 26:21.160
Everyone wins, no one loses.

26:23.040 --> 26:24.880
[Mintu] All right then, shake on it.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.720
[Order] Go on. Shake hands.

26:29.800 --> 26:31.320
- [Law] Well done.
- [Mintu] Excellent.

26:31.400 --> 26:33.200
[applause]

26:33.280 --> 26:35.720
- [Law] Well done.
- Excellent! [chuckles]

26:37.000 --> 26:38.520
SUJATA 14 MINTU 14

26:45.240 --> 26:47.120
[Munshi] That makes it 28.

26:47.200 --> 26:49.320
And after adding the two clients today…

26:51.800 --> 26:52.800
\30.

26:54.440 --> 26:57.320
Offering relief to 30 clients
in three months…

26:57.400 --> 26:58.960
Not even Tyagi managed that.

26:59.880 --> 27:02.280
- We won.
- [cheering]

27:03.040 --> 27:05.120
- [Sujata] Congrats.
- [Mintu] You too.

27:05.200 --> 27:06.240
[cheering continues]

27:06.320 --> 27:07.560
[chuckles]

27:10.080 --> 27:12.000
[chuckles]

27:18.040 --> 27:21.440
DISTRICT COURT, PATPARGANJ,
DELHI, SATYAMEV JAYATE

27:22.040 --> 27:26.160
- Uh, so this is…
- Vishwas, do you have a minute?

27:26.240 --> 27:27.840
Yeah, tell me, what is it?

27:27.920 --> 27:30.560
- [Sujata] Put that file back.
- File back? Yeah, all right.

27:30.640 --> 27:32.080
The thing is, ma'am, my brain is fried

27:32.160 --> 27:34.360
going "copy-copy"
on the walkie-talkie all morning.

27:34.440 --> 27:35.920
- So, um…
- [Sujata] All the best.

27:36.000 --> 27:37.400
- [Ani] Vishwas.
- Uh, uh…

27:38.680 --> 27:39.680
Uh…

27:39.760 --> 27:41.640
You know, Vishwas, I…

27:41.720 --> 27:45.600
All I said to Varsha was that
you prefer Mangesh's snacks.

27:45.680 --> 27:48.960
A-And the next thing Sujata tells me
is that your wedding is off.

27:49.040 --> 27:52.040
- Engagement. The engagement is off.
- Yeah.

27:52.640 --> 27:54.560
But it wasn't your fault. It's okay.

27:55.240 --> 27:57.800
But then, why are you ignoring me?

27:57.880 --> 27:59.480
No, I'm not ignoring you… I…

27:59.560 --> 28:01.320
Are we not friends anymore?

28:03.120 --> 28:05.320
Ani, It's because we're friends
that I'm ignoring you.

28:06.400 --> 28:08.280
You know, Varsha keeps telling me that,

28:08.920 --> 28:11.480
even if I am not in love with her,
that's okay.

28:12.200 --> 28:14.320
It's something that will happen
along the way.

28:14.400 --> 28:16.960
But if there is someone else,
then she is not okay with that.

28:17.040 --> 28:21.200
By someone else, she means me?

28:22.720 --> 28:24.840
Because I know your dietary preferences.

28:25.640 --> 28:29.120
Because she can see in our eyes
that there's a vibe between us.

28:29.920 --> 28:31.520
- [chuckles]
- [Ani clears throat]

28:31.600 --> 28:34.400
Vishwas, look into my eyes.

28:35.280 --> 28:36.480
Huh?

28:36.560 --> 28:39.240
[Ani] Look into my eyes. Look.

28:39.760 --> 28:41.560
- [sighs, chuckles]
- My eyes are here.

28:42.080 --> 28:43.520
- You're shifting your gaze.
- No.

28:51.440 --> 28:52.560
See something?

28:52.640 --> 28:53.840
Yeah.

28:55.120 --> 28:56.360
I did.

28:56.440 --> 28:57.440
What?

28:59.280 --> 29:00.920
There's a hair in your eye.

29:01.520 --> 29:02.680
[groans]

29:02.760 --> 29:03.760
- Ow.
- [blows]

29:03.840 --> 29:05.880
An eyelash. [chuckles] It's gone.

29:05.960 --> 29:07.440
[sighs] See?

29:08.120 --> 29:09.280
We're just friends.

29:10.080 --> 29:12.960
All you saw in my eyes
was an eyelash, dude.

29:13.040 --> 29:14.440
[chuckles]

29:14.520 --> 29:17.680
You know, you've always been there
for me when I needed you.

29:17.760 --> 29:22.240
And now when you need me, Vishwas,
then let me be there for you. Please.

29:23.880 --> 29:25.720
You can buy me a beer this evening.

29:27.000 --> 29:28.680
- You're nuts.
- No.

29:28.760 --> 29:30.400
- Come here.
- [chuckles, exclaims]

29:31.840 --> 29:34.080
Uh… after two weeks.

29:35.920 --> 29:37.080
Okay.

29:38.800 --> 29:40.360
Take care.

29:40.440 --> 29:42.200
Well the beer is arranged for.

29:42.280 --> 29:43.280
[chuckles]

29:54.320 --> 29:56.600
[phone buzzes]

30:03.240 --> 30:04.280
Mintu.

30:05.640 --> 30:08.720
What's up?
You're always on the phone these days.

30:08.000 --> 30:18.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

30:09.800 --> 30:11.320
Are you chatting with someone?

30:12.120 --> 30:14.720
Just a friend. Online.

30:14.800 --> 30:17.440
Oh, online. So you haven't met her?

30:17.960 --> 30:19.000
[sighs]

30:19.640 --> 30:22.760
Thing is, she's the really shy type.

30:23.800 --> 30:26.080
I've asked her out twice, but, uh…

30:26.160 --> 30:29.080
[inhales sharply] Third time lucky.
That's what they say.

30:31.720 --> 30:35.080
Just ask her.
I'm sure she'll agree this time.

30:41.120 --> 30:43.520
All the best. See you.

30:51.040 --> 30:52.560
[Patnaik] Congratulations, Tyagi.

30:52.640 --> 30:57.000
The highest number of cases resolved today
was at the Patparganj People's Court.

30:57.760 --> 31:01.320
With a capable judge like yourself,
that was bound to happen.

31:01.400 --> 31:03.920
- [chuckles]
- I'll always be indebted.

31:04.000 --> 31:05.080
Come on, don't say that,

31:05.160 --> 31:08.120
you call me a friend
and then say you are indebted.

31:08.200 --> 31:09.600
[chuckles] Here you go.

31:11.800 --> 31:14.080
I needed some advice from you, Mr Kela.

31:15.520 --> 31:16.520
Tell me.

31:19.320 --> 31:21.080
A friend of mine… [inhales sharply]

31:23.000 --> 31:25.680
…has been lying to me
for a very long time,

31:27.080 --> 31:28.160
taking advantage of me.

31:28.240 --> 31:30.960
So, what do you think I should do?

31:32.960 --> 31:35.800
There can be no place
for deceit in a friendship, Tyagi.

31:39.640 --> 31:40.920
Break off the friendship.

31:41.920 --> 31:46.240
And try not to take
his actions personally.

31:49.680 --> 31:52.880
You see, Tyagi, some people
are naturally inclined to slip up.

31:57.160 --> 31:58.160
And if that friend…

32:00.360 --> 32:03.800
has delivered verdicts
in over 2,000 cases…

32:05.040 --> 32:07.880
and toyed with the lives of
hundreds of people…

32:09.600 --> 32:10.880
then what should I do?

32:11.640 --> 32:13.960
[dramatic music plays]

32:14.040 --> 32:15.720
Does being a judge mean anything?

32:22.240 --> 32:24.280
Mean anything? [chuckles]

32:26.080 --> 32:29.360
You sit on a chair, look at some books,
and deliver a verdict.

32:31.240 --> 32:34.480
You advise people on what to do
and they start thinking of you as God.

32:36.160 --> 32:37.240
Isn't it, Tyagi?

32:37.760 --> 32:39.920
Until yesterday, I was Shubhkela.

32:40.720 --> 32:42.160
I was a capable judge.

32:43.000 --> 32:45.280
And today, as Sajjan Patnaik, I am a…

32:47.320 --> 32:48.320
[chuckles] …criminal.

32:48.960 --> 32:50.240
[chuckles]

32:50.320 --> 32:52.960
It's all an illusion, isn't it?

32:54.520 --> 32:55.720
What do you think?

32:56.400 --> 32:59.520
This justice, equality,

33:00.440 --> 33:02.720
for the people, by the people…

33:04.680 --> 33:05.800
all an illusion.

33:09.480 --> 33:11.920
If these principles meant anything,

33:13.280 --> 33:14.920
the world would be running on them.

33:16.120 --> 33:17.520
Isn't it, Tyagi?

33:23.680 --> 33:26.480
So what is it running on, Sajjan?

33:41.280 --> 33:42.320
Benefit.

33:45.080 --> 33:46.640
One's own benefit.

33:49.360 --> 33:52.800
Which is why, for me,
being a judge meant my acquittal.

33:54.600 --> 33:56.720
Just like for you, being a judge means…

33:58.640 --> 33:59.720
getting a kick.

34:03.520 --> 34:04.880
Right?

34:04.960 --> 34:06.960
[contemplative music plays]

34:20.160 --> 34:21.160
Let's go.
